{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_31","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n 'buildArgs|options|initialize-at-build-time|initialize-at-run-time|systemProperties|classInitialization|java.home' metadata tests -g 'reachability-metadata.json' -g '*.json' -g '*.properties'\"","aggregated_output":"metadata/io.suzaku/boopickle_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"BooPickle is a Scala binary serialization library for pickling and unpickling values into compact ByteBuffer data. It supports primitives, collections, options, tuples, case classes, custom serializers, references, and deduplication without reflection across JVM, Scala.js, and Scala Native.\",\nmetadata/commons-cli/commons-cli/index.json:22:    \"description\" : \"Apache Commons CLI provides a simple API for defining, processing, and validating command-line options in Java applications. It helps applications parse arguments, enforce option rules, and generate usage information.\"\nmetadata/org.iq80.leveldb/leveldb-api/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"leveldb-api provides the high-level Java API for interacting with LevelDB-style key-value databases. It defines the database, iterator, options, snapshot, and batch-write interfaces used by the iq80 pure-Java LevelDB implementation.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-protobuf-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlinx-serialization-protobuf-jvm is the JVM artifact of kotlinx.serialization's ProtoBuf format, providing APIs to encode and decode @Serializable Kotlin objects as Protocol Buffers binary data. It supports field-number annotations, integer encoding options, packed fields, oneof-style polymorphism, and schema generation for Kotlin/JVM applications using kotlinx.serialization.\",\nmetadata/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-core-grpc/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"google-cloud-core-grpc provides shared gRPC transport infrastructure for Google Cloud Java client libraries. It includes transport options, shared resource management, and base exception handling used by gRPC-based Google Cloud clients.\",\nmetadata/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-core/index.json:8:    \"description\" : \"Google Cloud Core provides shared foundational types and utilities used by Google Cloud Java client libraries, including service options, retry helpers, paging, IAM policy models, timestamps, and testing support. It supplies common abstractions for credentials, transport configuration, service RPC factories, and base service behavior so individual Google Cloud clients can share consistent runtime infrastructure.\",\nmetadata/com.google.cloud/google-cloud-core/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"Google Cloud Core provides shared abstractions and base types used by Google Cloud Java client libraries. It includes service options, retry helpers, paging, IAM policy, resource metadata, and other common infrastructure for building and using Google Cloud service clients.\",\nmetadata/net.sf.jopt-simple/jopt-simple/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"JOpt Simple is a Java library for parsing command-line options. It provides a fluent API for declaring accepted options, parsing arguments, and retrieving option values for command-line applications.\",\nmetadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json:205:              \"options\": {\nmetadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json:207:                \"title\": \"Linker options (see `java.lang.foreign.Linker.Option`)\",\nmetadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json:262:              \"options\": {\nmetadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json:264:                \"title\": \"Linker options (see `java.lang.foreign.Linker.Option`)\",\nmetadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json:265:                \"description\": \"Currently, no linker options are allowed for upcalls. This may change in the future.\",\nmetadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json:309:              \